1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new measure to gauge the complexity of image classification problems. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the correlation between the proposed metric and the test accuracy of convolutional neural networks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new method for assessing dataset complexity, which is relevant to the broader field of AI. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of probabilistic divergence in a spectral clustering framework. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks in evaluating the proposed metric.
